{
  "texts": [
    "This is a special case of the policy improvement theorem.",
    "Let two policies be π and π so that, for all s ∈ S, q π (s, π (s)) ≥ v π (s), the policy π must be as good as or better than π (i.e.",
    "π must have an expected reward greater than or equal to π), where v π (s) ≥ v π (s).",
    "This result applies particularly to the original policy π and the modified policy π.",
    "If q π (s, a) > v π (s), then the modified policy will be better than the original policy."
  ]
}